				\begin{document}$$\,{I} \, (\%)=({C}-{T})/({C}-{d})\times 100.$$\end{document}I(%)=(C−T)/(C−d)×100.where I is the inhibition rate (%), d is the diameter of the mycelium disc (5 mm). C and T are the average colony diameters of the mycelium of the control and treatment, respectively. The experiment was individually repeated at least thrice.

